quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  18,1,Praise is due only for God Who has sent down the book to His servant and has not kept any crookedness in it
  18,2,"(and has made it ) straight, that He may give warning of a severe punishment from Him, and ( convey ) good news to the believers who do righteous works, that for them there will be a good reward"
  18,3,in which they will stay for ever
  18,4,"and (also) warn those who say, “God has taken a son.”"
  18,5,"Neither they have any knowledge of it nor their fathers (had). (It is a) grievous word that comes out of their mouths, they speak nothing but a lie"
  18,6,"If they do not believe in this statement, then perhaps you will kill yourself with grief, sorrowing after them"
  18,7,"We have made that which is on the earth an adornment for it, so that We may test them as to which of them is best in conduct"
  18,8,"And We will make that which is on it, a barren ground"
  18,9,Or do you think that the companions of the cave and the inscription were a wonder from among Our signs
  18,10,"when the young men sought refuge in the cave and said, “Our Lord! give us mercy from Yourself and shape for us the right way in our affair?”"
  18,11,"So We prevented them from hearing (and kept them sleeping) in the cave, for a number of years"
  18,12,Then We raised them up that We might know (mark out) which of the two parties was better at calculating the time for which they stayed